verses.text_plain: The words of Jeremiah the son of Hilkiah, of the priests that were in Anathoth in the land of Benjamin:
verses.verse_html: 1The words of Jeremiah the son of Hilkiah, of the priests that were in Anathoth in the land of Benjamin:

verses.text_plain: To whom the word of the Lord came in the days of Josiah the son of Amon king of Judah, in the thirteenth year of his reign.
verses.verse_html: 2To whom the word of the Lord came in the days of Josiah the son of Amon king of Judah, in the thirteenth year of his reign.

verses.text_plain: It came also in the days of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah king of Judah, unto the end of the eleventh year of Zedekiah the son of Josiah king of Judah, unto the carrying away of Jerusalem captive in the fifth month.
verses.verse_html: 3It came also in the days of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah king of Judah, unto the end of the eleventh year of Zedekiah the son of Josiah king of Judah, unto the carrying away of Jerusalem captive in the fifth month.

tokens.text: It came also in the days

verses.text_plain: Then the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 4Then the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,

verses.text_plain: Before I formed thee in the belly I knew thee; and before thou camest forth out of the womb I sanctified thee, and I ordained thee a prophet unto the nations.
verses.verse_html:
5Before I formed thee in the belly I knew thee; and before thou camest forth out of the womb I sanctified thee, and I ordained thee a prophet unto the nations. ▼
▼ ordained: Heb. gave

tokens.text: thee; and before thou camest forth

verses.text_plain: Then said I, Ah, Lord God! behold, I cannot speak: for I am a child.
verses.verse_html: 6Then said I, Ah, Lord God! behold, I cannot speak: for I am a child.

verses.text_plain: But the Lord said unto me, Say not, I am a child: for thou shalt go to all that I shall send thee, and whatsoever I command thee thou shalt speak.
verses.verse_html: 7But the Lord said unto me, Say not, I am a child: for thou shalt go to all that I shall send thee, and whatsoever I command thee thou shalt speak.

tokens.text: to all that I shall send

verses.text_plain: Be not afraid of their faces: for I am with thee to deliver thee, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 8Be not afraid of their faces: for I am with thee to deliver thee, saith the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Then the Lord put forth his hand, and touched my mouth. And the Lord said unto me, Behold, I have put my words in thy mouth.
verses.verse_html: 9Then the Lord put forth his hand, and touched my mouth. And the Lord said unto me, Behold, I have put my words in thy mouth.

tokens.text: unto me, Behold, I have put

verses.text_plain: See, I have this day set thee over the nations and over the kingdoms, to root out, and to pull down, and to destroy, and to throw down, to build, and to plant.
verses.verse_html: 10See, I have this day set thee over the nations and over the kingdoms, to root out, and to pull down, and to destroy, and to throw down, to build, and to plant.

verses.text_plain: Moreover the word of the Lord came unto me, saying, Jeremiah, what seest thou? And I said, I see a rod of an almond tree.
verses.verse_html: 11Moreover the word of the Lord came unto me, saying, Jeremiah, what seest thou? And I said, I see a rod of an almond tree.

verses.text_plain: Then said the Lord unto me, Thou hast well seen: for I will hasten my word to perform it.
verses.verse_html: 12Then said the Lord unto me, Thou hast well seen: for I will hasten my word to perform it.

verses.text_plain: And the word of the Lord came unto me the second time, saying, What seest thou? And I said, I see a seething pot; and the face thereof is toward the north.
verses.verse_html:
13And the word of the Lord came unto me the second time, saying, What seest thou? And I said, I see a seething pot; and the face thereof is toward the north. ▼
▼ toward…: Heb. from the face of the north

footnotes.body_html: ▼ toward…: Heb. from the face of the north

verses.text_plain: Then the Lord said unto me, Out of the north an evil shall break forth upon all the inhabitants of the land.
verses.verse_html:
14Then the Lord said unto me, Out of the north an evil shall break forth upon all the inhabitants of the land. ▼
▼ shall…: Heb. shall be opened

tokens.text: unto me, Out of the north

footnotes.body_html: ▼ shall…: Heb. shall be opened

verses.text_plain: For, lo, I will call all the families of the kingdoms of the north, saith the Lord; and they shall come, and they shall set every one his throne at the entering of the gates of Jerusalem, and against all the walls thereof round about, and against all the cities of Judah.
verses.verse_html: 15For, lo, I will call all the families of the kingdoms of the north, saith the Lord; and they shall come, and they shall set every one his throne at the entering of the gates of Jerusalem, and against all the walls thereof round about, and against all the cities of Judah.

verses.text_plain: And I will utter my judgments against them touching all their wickedness, who have forsaken me, and have burned incense unto other gods, and worshipped the works of their own hands.
verses.verse_html: 16And I will utter my judgments against them touching all their wickedness, who have forsaken me, and have burned incense unto other gods, and worshipped the works of their own hands.

verses.text_plain: Thou therefore gird up thy loins, and arise, and speak unto them all that I command thee: be not dismayed at their faces, lest I confound thee before them.
verses.verse_html:
17Thou therefore gird up thy loins, and arise, and speak unto them all that I command thee: be not dismayed at their faces, lest I confound thee before them. ▼
▼ confound: or, break to pieces

tokens.text: unto them all that I command

footnotes.body_html: ▼ confound: or, break to pieces

verses.text_plain: For, behold, I have made thee this day a defenced city, and an iron pillar, and brasen walls against the whole land, against the kings of Judah, against the princes thereof, against the priests thereof, and against the people of the land.
verses.verse_html: 18For, behold, I have made thee this day a defenced city, and an iron pillar, and brasen walls against the whole land, against the kings of Judah, against the princes thereof, against the priests thereof, and against the people of the land.

verses.text_plain: And they shall fight against thee; but they shall not prevail against thee; for I am with thee, saith the Lord, to deliver thee.
verses.verse_html: 19And they shall fight against thee; but they shall not prevail against thee; for I am with thee, saith the Lord, to deliver thee.

tokens.text: against thee; but they shall not prevail
